compliance_reasoning: This regulation (112) specifically governs permitted contact times with consumers by telephone or visit. The document provided is a pension life cover scheme rules document that outlines the structure, definitions, and operation of a pension scheme. It does not contain any provisions related to contacting consumers by telephone or visit. The document is focused on defining the scheme's structure, benefits, and trustee responsibilities rather than operational procedures for contacting consumers. There is no content in the document that would be subject to the time restrictions for consumer contact specified in Regulation 112.
regulation_title: Permitted contact by telephone or visit to be made only during certain times
regulation_text: 112. Permitted contact with a consumer, by telephone or by visit, made in accordance with these Regulations, may be made only between 9.00 a.m. and 9.00 p.m. Monday to Saturday, excluding public holidays, unless otherwise agreed in writing with the consumer.
source_name: CENTRAL BANK (SUPERVISION AND ENFORCEMENT) ACT 2013 (SECTION 48) (CONSUMER PROTECTION) REGULATIONS 2025
